Auroral Electrojet (AE) Index
A high-latitude geomagnetic index measuring the influence of auroral currents that create surface magnetic field deviations measured in nanoTesla. AE characterizes the maximum excursion (+ and -) from quiet levels. Typically, data from ~ a dozen northern hemisphere stations are used: AE = AU ‚Äì AL. AU (upper) refers to the most positive deviation and AL (lower) to the most negative. AO refers to the mean: = 1/2 (AU + AL). AE and companion indexes are at http://wdc.kugi.kyoto-u.ac.jp/wdc/Sec3.html
