Bow Shock
A shock wave formed in a plasma stream when it comes upon a barrier such as the Earth‚Äôs magnetosphere. The bow shock deflects, slows and heats the incoming plasma. So-named because of its similarity to the curved ‚Äúbow wave‚Äù which forms in the water ahead of the bow of a moving ship
