Geocorona
The envelope of escaped hydrogen that surrounds the Earth. Originally thought to extend only a few Earth radii beyond Earth‚Äôs surface, recent images show a faint glow extending beyond the Moon‚Äôs orbit. The geocorona produces a faint ultraviolet glow in hydrogen Lyman-alpha (Ly-ùû™) at ~121.6 nm
