Geomagnetic Storm (GMS)
A severe but transitory fluctuation in the Earth‚Äôs magnetic field, evident initially as a sharp decrease in the strength of the horizontal component of the Earth‚Äôs magnetic field, felt around the world and lasting a few hours, followed by a recovery phase lasting a day to several days. Geomagnetic storms are most often initiated when regions of enhanced solar wind flow compress the steady-state form of the magnetosphere on its Sun-facing side
