Ground Level Enhancement (GLE)
A category of extreme solar energetic particle (SEP) events. During such events there are a sufficient number of energetic ions with energy above ~500 MeV, which interact with the Earth‚Äôs atmosphere to create quantities of secondary neutrons and/or muons measurable by ground‚Äêbased instrumentation.
GLEs generally associate with particles energized by fast CMEs. GLE onset is within a few minutes after the eruption begins.
