Magnetotail
The extension of the magnetosphere in the anti-sunward direction as a result of interaction with the solar wind. In the inner magnetotail, the field lines maintain a roughly dipolar configuration. At greater distances, the field lines are stretched into northern and southern lobes, separated by a plasmasheet. There is observational evidence for traces of the Earth‚Äôs magnetotail as far as 1000 Earth radii downstream.
